</svg>

<!-- HERO + DEMO -->
<div class="hero">
  <nav>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="logo"><svg viewBox="0 0 128 128" style="width:30px;height:30px;border-radius:8px;" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#deck-export-icon"/></svg>Deck Export</div>
      <div class="navlinks">
        <a href="#how">How it works</a>
        <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
      </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="hero-inner wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow on-dark">A plugin for Figma</div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">From Figma to Google Slides in 30 seconds</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Build your deck in your usual Figma template — export turns it into a fully editable slide deck. No screenshots, no manual rebuilding.</p>
    <p class="micro" style="margin-top:16px;">Free · Works right inside Figma</p>
  </div>

  <div class="demo-stage wrap">
    <div class="demo-frame-wrap">
      <div class="top-pill-row">
        <div class="pill">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16" rx="3"/><path d="M9 9h6v6H9z"/></svg>
          Live demo
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="browser-frame">
        <div class="browser-bar"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
        <div class="browser-video">
          <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="assets/deck-export-demo-poster.jpg">
            <source src="assets/deck-export-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4">
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-pill-row">
        <div class="step-pill">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="color:#fff"><path d="M4 4l7 16 2-7 7-2z"/></svg>
          Select frame
        </div>
        <span class="arrow-sep">→</span>
        <div class="step-pill">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="color:#fff"><path d="M12 3v12M7 8l5-5 5 5M5 21h14"/></svg>
          Export
        </div>
        <span class="arrow-sep">→</span>
        <div class="step-pill">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="color:#fff"><path d="M12 20h9M16.5 3.5a2.1 2.1 0 013 3L7 19l-4 1 1-4z"/></svg>
          Keep editing
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="wordmark">Deck Export</div>
</div>

<!-- PROBLEM -->
<section id="problem">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">Sound familiar?</div>
    <h2 class="problem-title">Design lives in Figma. The client is waiting for a Google Slides deck.</h2>
    <div class="pain-grid">
      <div class="pain-card">
        <div class="pain-num">01</div>
        <p>Design was built in Figma — but sales needs it in Google Slides, because that's where the deck actually goes to the client.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-card">
        <div class="pain-num">02</div>
        <p>Manual transfer means either screenshots (no longer editable) or rebuilding every slide by hand — an hour or more per deck.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-card">
        <div class="pain-num">03</div>
        <p>Every last-minute edit means another cycle: rework it in Figma → transfer it by hand again.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="transition-line">We ran into this ourselves — so we built a tool that closes this gap in one click.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SOLUTION -->
<section id="how" style="background:var(--paper-2);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">How it works</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px); margin-top:14px;">One plugin. Three steps.</h2>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-n">01</div>
        <h3>Build your deck in Figma</h3>
        <p>In your usual template, the way you always work — no new rules or structures.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-n">02</div>
        <h3>Click export</h3>
        <p>It automatically turns every frame/slide in Figma into a Google Slides slide.</p>
      </div>
